<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="bmaster-sitename">BMaster SiteName</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <p><strong>BMaster</strong> is the <em>SiteName</em> of the beekeeping education and management site hosted on this Comserv installation. As a Comserv site, it behaves identically to any other hosted site (MCoop, HelpDesk, etc.) — it is identified by the <code>SiteName = 'BMaster'</code> session variable and receives its own theme, navigation menus, and member roles.</p>
        <p>The entry point for the BMaster site is:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/BMaster"><code>/BMaster</code></a> — site home page, served by <code>Controller::BMaster::index</code>, renders <code>BMaster/BMaster.tt</code></li>
        </ul>
        <p>The <code>BMaster.pm</code> controller retains the site home and chained base, but all beekeeping <em>feature</em> actions have been moved to <code>Controller::Beekeeping</code>. The old <code>/BMaster/*</code> feature URLs remain as backward-compatible redirect stubs.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="beekeeping-feature">Beekeeping Feature — Separation from SiteName (May 2026)</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <p>Prior to May 2026, all beekeeping feature routes lived under <code>/BMaster/*</code> in <code>Controller::BMaster</code>. This created an architectural ambiguity: <em>BMaster</em> meant both the Comserv SiteName and the beekeeping application feature.</p>
        <p>The refactoring introduced a dedicated <strong><code>Controller::Beekeeping</code></strong> hierarchy. All beekeeping feature URLs now live under <code>/Beekeeping/*</code>. The old <code>/BMaster/*</code> URLs issue HTTP 302 redirects to the canonical <code>/Beekeeping/*</code> equivalents so existing bookmarks and external links continue to work.</p>
        <p>The Apiary management system (logged-in member tools) continues to live under <code>/Apiary/*</code> in <code>Controller::Apiary</code> — this was not changed.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="controller-hierarchy">Controller Hierarchy</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Controller</th><th>Path Prefix</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::BMaster</code></td>
                    <td><code>/BMaster</code></td>
                    <td>BMaster site home + backward-compat redirect stubs for old <code>/BMaster/*</code> URLs</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::Beekeeping</code></td>
                    <td><code>/Beekeeping</code></td>
                    <td>Beekeeping feature hub — public info pages (apiary, environment, education, products)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::Beekeeping::Yards</code></td>
                    <td><code>/Beekeeping/yards</code>, <code>/Beekeeping/add_yard</code></td>
                    <td>Yard listing and creation (member tool)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::Beekeeping::Health</code></td>
                    <td><code>/Beekeeping/health</code></td>
                    <td>Bee health information page</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::Beekeeping::Harvest</code></td>
                    <td><code>/Beekeeping/harvest</code></td>
                    <td>Honey production and harvest page</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>Controller::Apiary</code></td>
                    <td><code>/Apiary</code></td>
                    <td>Full apiary management system (inspections, hives, queens) — requires login</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

