                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping::Inspection</code></td><td><code>inspections</code></td><td>Hive inspection records</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping::InspectionDetail</code></td><td><code>inspection_details</code></td><td>Per-box/frame inspection observations</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping::InspectionFeeding</code></td><td><code>inspection_feedings</code></td><td>Feeding records linked to inspections</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping::HoneyHarvest</code></td><td><code>honey_harvests</code></td><td>Harvest records per hive</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="navigation">Navigation</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <p>The beekeeping menu is defined in <code>root/Navigation/TopDropListBeekeeping.tt</code>. It is included by <code>pagetop.tt</code> when the site or member has the beekeeping module enabled.</p>
        <p>Visibility rules:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>enabled_modules.beekeeping</code> — member opted into the beekeeping feature</li>
            <li><code>enabled_modules.apiary</code> — site-level apiary module enabled</li>
            <li><code>SiteName == 'BMaster'</code> — always shown on the BMaster site</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Link strategy in the menu:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Guests (not logged in)</strong> — info and advertising pages under <code>/Beekeeping/*</code></li>
            <li><strong>Members (logged in)</strong> — working management pages under <code>/Apiary/*</code></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="dev-notes">Developer Notes</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <h3>Adding a new Beekeeping feature page</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Add an action to <code>Controller::Beekeeping</code> (or a new sub-controller under <code>Controller::Beekeeping/</code>) using <code>:Path('/Beekeeping/your-route')</code>.</li>
            <li>Create the template in <code>root/Beekeeping/your-template.tt</code>. Follow the theme compliance rules in <code>root/Documentation/ApplicationTtTemplate.tt</code>: use <code>app-container</code>, <code>app-section</code>, <code>content-section</code> CSS classes.</li>
            <li>Add the route to <code>root/Navigation/TopDropListBeekeeping.tt</code> if it belongs in the nav menu.</li>
            <li>Update this documentation.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Backward-compat redirect pattern</h3>
        <p>When renaming or moving a route, keep the old URL as a redirect stub in the original controller. Example pattern used in <code>BMaster.pm</code>:</p>
        <pre class="code-block">sub old_name :Path('/OldPath/action') :Args(0) {
    my ($self, $c) = @_;
    $self->logging->log_with_details($c, 'info', __FILE__, __LINE__, 'old_name', "old_name → /NewPath/action");
    $c->response->redirect('/NewPath/action');
}</pre>

        <h3>Guest vs member routing pattern</h3>
        <p>Public info pages are served from <code>Controller::Beekeeping</code>. Member management tools live in <code>Controller::Apiary</code>. The <code>/Beekeeping/apiary</code> action demonstrates the guest/member split:</p>
        <pre class="code-block">if ($c->session->{user_id}) {
    $c->response->redirect($c->uri_for('/Apiary'));
} else {
    $c->stash(template => 'Beekeeping/apiary.tt');
}</pre>

        <h3>Verification</h3>
        <p>After any change to a controller or model, run:</p>
        <pre class="code-block">perl -cw Comserv/script/comserv_server.pl</pre>
    </div>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
